    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-07-19T11:37:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-07-19T11:37:00-05:00" n="422"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d422">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">683.84A/7–1951: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_AWR1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-07-19T12:37:00-04:00"
                            >July 19, 1951—12:37 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>110. Re Syrian-Israeli Dispute. Re Usun 93, July 16.<note n="1" xml:id="d422fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_773">p. 773</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>We suggest for Dept’s consideration following program of action re Syrian-Israeli
                    dispute over Huleh drainage project: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>An effort to persuade <persName corresp="#p_RWE1">Riley</persName>,
                            having consulted in NY, to return to Palestine and make one more strong
                            try to iron out differences and bring parties together for solution this
                            dispute. <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> meanwhile would not be
                            convened. Before returning to Palestine, <persName corresp="#p_RWE1"
                                >Riley</persName> might file report he now has in mind reciting
                            facts in situation as he now sees them but indicating that he is
                            returning to Palestine after consultation here for purpose indicated. It
                            may, of course, be very difficult to persuade <persName
                                corresp="#p_RWE1">Riley</persName> to follow this course since in
                            his present mood it seems clear that he wants to leave the baby on the
                                <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>’s doorstep. If <persName
                                corresp="#p_RWE1">Riley</persName> should, before returning to
                            Palestine, file a report of the nature he apparently has in mind, it
                            would be very difficult to avoid council mtg at this point; it might,
                            therefore, be preferable if <persName corresp="#p_RWE1">Riley</persName>
                            refrained from issuing a further report at this time.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>If <persName corresp="#p_RWE1">Riley</persName> is unwilling to return
                            to Palestine as indicated above or if he should return and his mission
                            should result in failure, <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> might take
                            up matter with view to following action. <list>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Reaffirmation and clarification of essential parts of May 18
                                    resolutions (in order strengthen <persName corresp="#p_RWE1"
                                        >Riley</persName>’s hands) and <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                                        >SC</gloss> request to him to renew his effort.</item>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                                <item>In order assist <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> in its
                                    consideration of problem since it appears to have ramifications
                                    concerning water supply for entire Jordan area, <gloss
                                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> might request <persName
                                        corresp="#p_BJB2">Blandford</persName> (with assistance, if
                                    needed, of technical experts provided by <gloss target="#t_SYG1"
                                        >SYG</gloss>) to study and report to <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                                        >SC</gloss> as matter of urgency on economic and related
                                    implications, including problem of refugee resettlement. In view
                                    of previous studies which have been made and <persName
                                        corresp="#p_BJB2">Blandford</persName>’s knowledge of
                                    General situation, he should be able to produce such report in
                                    relatively brief time.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AWR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
